00008 std::string unparseX86Mnemonic(SgAsmx86Instruction *insn) {
00009     ROSE_ASSERT(insn!=NULL);
00010     std::string result;
00011     if (insn->get_lockPrefix())
00012         result += "lock ";
00013     result += insn->get_mnemonic();
00014     switch (insn->get_branchPrediction()) {
00015         case x86_branch_prediction_none: break;
00016         case x86_branch_prediction_taken: result += ",pt"; break;
00017         case x86_branch_prediction_not_taken: result += ",pn"; break;
00018         default: ROSE_ASSERT (!"Bad branch prediction");
00019     }
00020     return result;
00021 }

00088 std::string unparseX86Expression(SgAsmExpression *expr, const AsmUnparser::LabelMap *labels, bool leaMode) {
00089     std::string result = "";
00090     if (expr == NULL) return "BOGUS:NULL";
00091 
00092     switch (expr->variantT()) {
00093         case V_SgAsmBinaryAdd:
00094             result = unparseX86Expression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_lhs(), labels, false) + " + " +
00095                      unparseX86Expression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_rhs(), labels, false);
00096             break;
00097 
00098         case V_SgAsmBinarySubtract:
00099             result = unparseX86Expression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_lhs(), labels, false) + " - " +
00100                      unparseX86Expression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_rhs(), labels, false);
00101             break;
00102 
00103         case V_SgAsmBinaryMultiply:
00104             result = unparseX86Expression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_lhs(), labels, false) + "*" +
00105                      unparseX86Expression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_rhs(), labels, false);
00106             break;
00107 
00108         case V_SgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression: {
00109             SgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression* mr = isSgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression(expr);
00110             if (!leaMode) {
00111                 result += x86TypeToPtrName(mr->get_type()) + " PTR " +
00112                           (mr->get_segment() ? unparseX86Expression(mr->get_segment(), labels, false) + ":" : "");
00113             }
00114             result += "[" + unparseX86Expression(mr->get_address(), labels, false) + "]";
00115             break;
00116         }
00117 
00118         case V_SgAsmx86RegisterReferenceExpression: {
00119             SgAsmx86RegisterReferenceExpression* rr = isSgAsmx86RegisterReferenceExpression(expr);
00120             result = unparseX86Register(rr->get_descriptor());
00121             break;
00122         }
00123 
00124         case V_SgAsmByteValueExpression:
00125         case V_SgAsmWordValueExpression:
00126         case V_SgAsmDoubleWordValueExpression:
00127         case V_SgAsmQuadWordValueExpression:
00128         case V_SgAsmIntegerValueExpression: {
00129             SgAsmIntegerValueExpression *ival = isSgAsmIntegerValueExpression(expr);
00130             assert(ival!=NULL);
00131             uint64_t value = ival->get_absolute_value(); // not sign extended
00132             result = StringUtility::addrToString(value, ival->get_significant_bits(), true/*signed*/);
00133 
00134             // Optional label.  Prefer a label supplied by the caller's LabelMap, but not for single-byte constants.  If
00135             // there's no caller-supplied label, then consider whether the value expression is relative to some other IR node.
00136             std::string label;
00137             if (ival->get_significant_bits()>8)
00138                 label =x86ValToLabel(value, labels);
00139             if (label.empty())
00140                 label = ival->get_label();
00141             if (!label.empty())
00142                 result += "<" + label + ">";
00143             break;
00144         }
00145 
00146         default: {
00147             std::cerr << "Unhandled expression kind " << expr->class_name() << std::endl;
00148             ROSE_ASSERT (false);
00149         }
00150     }
00151 
00152     if (expr->get_replacement() != "") {
00153         result += " <" + expr->get_replacement() + ">";
00154     }
00155 #if 0
00156     if (expr->get_bit_size()>0) {
00157         result += " <@" + StringUtility::numberToString(expr->get_bit_offset()) +
00158                   "+" + StringUtility::numberToString(expr->get_bit_size()) + ">";
00159     }
00160 #endif
00161     return result;
00162 }

00165 std::string unparseX86Expression(SgAsmExpression *expr, const AsmUnparser::LabelMap *labels) {
00166     /* Find the instruction with which this expression is associated. */
00167     SgAsmx86Instruction *insn = NULL;
00168     for (SgNode *node=expr; !insn && node; node=node->get_parent()) {
00169         insn = isSgAsmx86Instruction(node);
00170     }
00171     ROSE_ASSERT(insn!=NULL);
00172     return unparseX86Expression(expr, labels, insn->get_kind()==x86_lea);
00173 }
